body: Excuse me, how to reproduce this bug? Do you think it is a bug for the ScatterND kernel?

it's happening when referencing PaddlOCR recognition model which is a converted model from PaddlePaddle.

You can download or test it from the github repo:  https://github.com/znsoftm/RapidOCR

> Excuse me, how to reproduce this bug? Do you think it is a bug for the ScatterND kernel?


Eh......... ,   I  think  it is onnxruntime's bug .  
Because,  have much bug  like  'Non-zero status code returned while running Reshape node. Name:'Reshape_502' , I do not know how to solve 。

> it's happening when referencing PaddlOCR recognition model which is a converted model from PaddlePaddle.
> 
> You can download or test it from the github repo: https://github.com/znsoftm/RapidOCR


I use pytorch rewrite  discern model of  PaddleOcr , it can run on onnxruntime 。
But new bug happen ， like  ' Non-zero status code returned while running Reshape node. Name:Reshape_502  ' or 
' Non-zero status code returned while running Add node.  ' 

Use pytorch and export onnx :
=================
code:   y[:, :, ::2, ::2] = x
error:  Non-zero status code returned while running Reshape node. Name:Reshape_502

=================
code :   in4 + F.upsample(in5, scale_factor=2, mode="nearest")
error  :  Non-zero status code returned while running Add node.
Please look back to our github, yes , it's RapidOCR, we  released a version of new Paddle2Onnx ( from original author)
It's only a bug of Paddle2Onnx. Please add me into you wechat, 364479
I'll close it because it is more likely a converter bug. If @znsoftm were wrong, please reopen.
